children.name: Text
children.value: Do you need a lesson in manners from a pirate?

children.name: Text
children.value: I bet that will sting for days.

children.name: Text
children.value: Wish I could have seen their face.

children.name: Text
children.value: Hey, I'll play the trickster around here‚Ä¶

children.name: Text
children.value: At least try to keep your cards close to your chest!

children.name: Text
children.value: Now that is a very clever thing indeed!

children.name: Text
children.value: Please, don't let me stop you!

children.name: Text
children.value: It's easier if you don‚Äôt fight!

children.name: Text
children.value: You didn't have to do this.

children.name: Text
children.value: Someone had to take the fall.

children.name: Text
children.value: Not the first gamble that didn't pay.

children.name: Text
children.value: It was begging to be knocked down.

children.name: Text
children.value: You have to learn to manage your anger!

children.name: Text
children.value: Come on, that's an inanimate object!

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm sorry it had to be this way, but fish have to eat if they want to avoid being eaten.

children.name: Text
children.value: You shield us like a cloak.

children.name: Text
children.value: You've shaken off quite a hindrance.

children.name: Text
children.value: Got to keep your options open.

children.name: Text
children.value: Everybody needs some kind of protection.

children.name: Text
children.value: We all have something to preserve.

children.name: Text
children.value: Please - you have a duty to your people.

children.name: Text
children.value: I see your cards, and you don't have much.

children.name: Text
children.value: I thought you were above that.

children.name: Text
children.value: Our whole plan depends on you still being with us.

children.name: Text
children.value: Will you protect me and my family as you said you would?

children.name: Text
children.value: We are at war with your ally, let us see your true colours.

children.name: Text
children.value: Of course friend, whatever you need.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is a big risk for us, but wi, we will fight for you.

children.name: Text
children.value: They take up arms for the freedom of their colour.

children.name: Text
children.value: They pray morning and evening this war will end.

children.name: Text
children.value: We desire only to defend these properties and the families that inhabit them.

children.name: Text
children.value: You found one ship, but others are on the move.

children.name: Text
children.value: War is bad for you, we have allies everywhere.

children.name: Text
children.value: They'll lay down arms the moment you make a fair peace offer.

children.name: Text
children.value: As old dreams die, new ones take shape.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't worry, we'll hide out as long as we need to.

children.name: Text
children.value: This time, I'm going to get in with the right people.

children.name: Text
children.value: We've rebuilt before, we can do it again.

children.name: Text
children.value: The past is the past, the future is ours to protect.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't let anyone treat me like that.

children.name: Text
children.value: You won't keep them down forever.

children.name: Text
children.value: George supported me, so I support him!

children.name: Text
children.value: Make him suffer as he made my people suffer.

children.name: Text
children.value: George is an ally you can rely on.

children.name: Text
children.value: If you support Silva, you support La Corona.

children.name: Text
children.value: I can recongnise a cruel master.

children.name: Text
children.value: You do what you have to, to protect your own.

children.name: Text
children.value: Believe me I share Isabel's cause, but I already have enough trouble with the Empire.

children.name: Text
children.value: I beg you, I don't want to live in a world of Pyrphorians. Make them go away.

children.name: Text
children.value: Phew! That's one less threat to our survival that I have to take care of!

children.name: Text
children.value: Please‚Äî we'll take any help we can get.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your chance to fight for something worth fighting for.

children.name: Text
children.value: These people, they need a hero.

children.name: Text
children.value: Bring us the horizon, where the fire of freedom rises.

children.name: Text
children.value: We're always looking to those we can trust.

children.name: Text
children.value: Without you, I don't know what we would have done.

children.name: Text
children.value: You have done a beautiful thing this day.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your brave actions may just have saved us.

children.name: Text
children.value: Tell me, did they get to you?

children.name: Text
children.value: Any way the wind blows, eh? We will be better without you.

children.name: Text
children.value: The hopes of a generation, crushed.

children.name: Text
children.value: Do you mean to sabotage us?

children.name: Text
children.value: Not all will last in the struggle.

children.name: Text
children.value: Do not turn your back on this fight!

children.name: Text
children.value: There is a time for waiting, it is not now!

children.name: Text
children.value: Do it now, while the moon lights the river.

children.name: Text
children.value: This struggle, it is never over.

children.name: Text
children.value: Freedom is so close, help us push through.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is in all of us to support the underdog.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't be a fool, listen to your heart.

children.name: Text
children.value: Ol√°. Tell me it's good news?

children.name: Text
children.value: What I have would take too long to explain‚Ä¶

children.name: Text
children.value: I must plan our next move.

children.name: Text
children.value: Better keep our heads down for a while.

children.name: Text
children.value: Look after my people, they are all I have.

children.name: Text
children.value: We must protect the vulnerable who cross the seas.

children.name: Text
children.value: So, you found us. Take a look around. What can the henchmen of the Empire do to us that the Pyrphorians haven't already?

children.name: Text
children.value: Goode? The man that sold Her Majesty's precious island to me? He is just as guilty as I am!

children.name: Text
children.value: So you are calling me as a liar? Love is blind. Back before they left their fiery mark, the Pyrphorians told me your father would come‚Äî to sell me Prosperity.

children.name: Text
children.value: I knew conspiring against the Empire was a bad idea. Afterwards, when I refused to work with the Pyrphorians, they came to teach us a lesson.

children.name: Text
children.value: Now our movement drills their oil for nothing, night and day. We have lost the strength to fight.

children.name: Text
children.value: Still we are afraid. And even though we buried the dead and found a hideaway, I cannot provide shelter for all of them.

children.name: Text
children.value: So you won't let go? Then let's get to business. Help me shelter and protect the good people that are part of this movement. If I see you can be trusted, I will find you the treaty that sealed the deal on Prosperity. Are you in?

children.name: Text
children.value: Then we too were betrayed. We will leave Prosperity immediately, your Majesty.

children.name: Text
children.value: They are more than a nuisance! And they will never accept this. You must be careful!

children.name: Text
children.value: Build us a haven on La Isla, and we can talk about getting you that contract.

children.name: Text
children.value: We will help you. But first you have to help us.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Pyrphorians would only exploit us if we tried to resettle ourselves. But with an island under your flag‚Ä¶

children.name: Text
children.value: This place is more than good enough for us. We are used to living on very little.

children.name: Text
children.value: They are mostly just civilians, hoping for somewhere they can feel safe.

children.name: Text
children.value: This can be our fortress. A beautiful garden away from terrible things. We must protect it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Once this is over I promise to repay you. Right now, I care about my people's safety!

children.name: Text
children.value: We must be ready for the Pyrphorians if they come.

children.name: Text
children.value: You could make the resistance yet! We are grateful to have such security now.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're doing amazing work. Together we will fight them with everything we have!
